---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Admin Studio — RevenueUp" description="RevenueUp content and operations studio." appMode={true}>
<section class="admin-shell" data-admin><aside class="admin-sidebar"><a class="brand" href="/"><span class="brand-mark">R</span><span>Revenue<span>Up</span></span></a><nav><button class="active" data-tab="dashboard">⌂ Overview</button><button data-tab="blog">✎ Blog Studio</button><button data-tab="telegram">↗ Telegram</button><a href="/blog">◎ View blog</a><a href="/">← Website</a></nav><div class="admin-user"><div>RV</div><span><b>Administrator</b><small>Content studio</small></span></div></aside>
<main class="admin-main"><header class="admin-topbar"><button class="admin-menu">☰</button><div><small>REVENUEUP CONTROL CENTER</small><h1 data-page-title>Overview</h1></div><span class="admin-badge">STATIC + SECURE API</span></header>
<section class="admin-panel active" data-panel="dashboard"><div class="admin-stat-grid"><article><span>CONTENT</span><b>Markdown</b><small>Portable blog files</small></article><article><span>PUBLISHING</span><b>Git-based</b><small>Upload, commit, deploy</small></article><article><span>LEADS</span><b>Telegram</b><small>Server-side delivery</small></article></div><div class="admin-dashboard-grid"><article class="admin-card"><small>QUICK START</small><h2>Publish your next insight</h2><ol class="publish-flow"><li><b>Write</b><span>Create and preview in Blog Studio.</span></li><li><b>Download</b><span>Export a ready-to-publish .md file.</span></li><li><b>Upload</b><span>Add to <code>src/content/blog/</code>.</span></li><li><b>Deploy</b><span>Cloudflare publishes on build.</span></li></ol><button class="button" data-open-blog>Write article ↗</button></article><article class="admin-card"><small>SYSTEM STATUS</small><h2>Deployment checklist</h2><div class="status-row"><span>Blog collection</span><b class="ok">READY</b></div><div class="status-row"><span>Blog routes</span><b class="ok">READY</b></div><div class="status-row"><span>Contact API</span><b>CONFIGURE</b></div><div class="status-row"><span>Cloudflare Access</span><b>RECOMMENDED</b></div></article></div></section>
<section class="admin-panel" data-panel="blog"><div class="editor-toolbar"><div><span class="eyebrow">BLOG STUDIO</span><h2>Create a publish-ready article</h2></div><div><label class="import-button">Import .md<input type="file" accept=".md,.mdx" data-import/></label><button class="button" data-download>Download .md ↓</button></div></div><div class="blog-editor-grid"><form class="editor-form" data-editor-form><div class="field-row"><label>Article title<input name="title" required placeholder="A clear headline"/></label><label>URL slug<input name="slug" required placeholder="article-slug"/></label></div><label>Description<textarea name="description" rows="2" required placeholder="One concise promise"></textarea></label><div class="field-row three"><label>Category<input name="category" value="Growth Strategy"/></label><label>Author<input name="author" value="RevenueUp Editorial"/></label><label>Publish date<input name="publishDate" type="date"/></label></div><div class="field-row"><label>Tags<input name="tags" placeholder="growth, strategy"/></label><label>Cover image URL<input name="cover" placeholder="https://..."/></label></div><div class="check-row"><label><input type="checkbox" name="featured"/> Featured</label><label><input type="checkbox" name="draft"/> Draft</label></div><label>SEO title<input name="seoTitle"/></label><label>SEO description<textarea name="seoDescription" rows="2"></textarea></label><label class="content-field">Article content <span>Markdown supported</span><textarea name="content" rows="22" placeholder="# Start with a strong idea..."></textarea></label></form><aside class="preview-pane"><div class="preview-top"><span>LIVE PREVIEW</span><div><button data-view="desktop" class="active">Desktop</button><button data-view="mobile">Mobile</button></div></div><article data-preview><span class="preview-category">Growth Strategy</span><h1>Your article title</h1><p class="preview-description">Your description appears here.</p><div class="preview-meta">RevenueUp Editorial · Today</div><div class="preview-content"><p>Start writing to preview your article.</p></div></article></aside></div><div class="publish-help"><b>Upload destination</b><code>src/content/blog/&lt;your-slug&gt;.md</code><p>Commit the downloaded file to GitHub. Cloudflare will publish it automatically.</p></div></section>
<section class="admin-panel" data-panel="telegram"><div class="telegram-grid"><article class="admin-card"><span class="eyebrow">SECURE DELIVERY</span><h2>Telegram lead notifications</h2><p>Contact submissions go through a Cloudflare Function. The bot token never reaches the browser.</p><div class="secure-flow"><div>Contact form</div><span>→</span><div>Cloudflare API</div><span>→</span><div>Telegram bot</div></div><label>Admin API secret<input type="password" data-admin-secret placeholder="ADMIN_SECRET"/></label><button class="button" data-test-telegram>Test connection ↗</button><p data-test-result></p></article><article class="admin-card setup-card"><small>CLOUDFLARE VARIABLES</small><h2>Configure once</h2><div><b>TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN</b><code>123456:ABC...</code></div><div><b>TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID</b><code>-1001234567890</code></div><div><b>ADMIN_SECRET</b><code>Long random value</code></div><p>Add under Cloudflare Pages → Settings → Environment variables, then redeploy.</p><div class="security-note"><b>Never expose tokens</b><span>Do not place secrets in Astro pages, public JS or GitHub.</span></div></article></div></section>
</main></section><script is:inline src="/admin.js"></script>
</Base>
